The paper deals with game theory and optimization, which are central topics in cs.GT (Game Theory and Economics) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The use of probabilities and stochastic demands suggests a connection to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deal with uncertainty and randomness. Finally, the paper also involves optimization techniques and the derivation of analytic expressions, which are relevant to cs.IT (Information Theory).
